{"content": "<p>Artists and artworks get discovered...and forgotten and sometimes rediscovered again. </p><p>Today's MintFace features an artist and artwork and a sale with the discovery theme.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.45.36-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1672\" height=\"1672\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.45.36-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.45.36-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.45.36-PM.png 1600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.45.36-PM.png 1672w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><h3 id=\"mintface-artist-featurerachel-creasey\">MintFace Artist Feature - Rachel Creasey</h3><p>Rachel is an artist with New Zealand origins who shifted to London to become Fine Art trained at the Wimbledon School of Art in London. She's back in New Zealand now, at least for the time being like many Kiwi's, able to continue life mostly as normal through the pandemic.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/nft.png.jpeg\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1680\" height=\"1120\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/nft.png.jpeg 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/08/nft.png.jpeg 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/08/nft.png.jpeg 1600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/nft.png.jpeg 1680w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"><figcaption><a href=\"https://foundation.app/@raecreate/match-point-57124\">Match Point - by Rachel Creasey</a>, recently sold to a collector on Foundation</figcaption></figure><blockquote>\"Light doesn't always travel in a straight line. It can be bent, like the truth, to serve our own purposes.  Ultimately, who can we look to to discern the real truth? Only ourselves.\"</blockquote><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/nft-5.jpg\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1680\" height=\"1260\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/nft-5.jpg 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/08/nft-5.jpg 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/08/nft-5.jpg 1600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/nft-5.jpg 1680w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"><figcaption>Study In Yellow - Rachel Creasey, <a href=\"https://foundation.app/@raecreate/study-in-yellow-51981\">Foundation marketplace</a></figcaption></figure><p>I discovered her work after my Mum mentioned an artist in her Instagram newsfeed had created an NFT! It turned out to be <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/raecreateart/\">Rachel's Instagram</a>. Rachel's work has plenty of fans of her work on Twitter as well.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">I always enjoy your photography and the way you look at the ordinary and make it extraordinary. <a href=\"https://t.co/yt9aNp5vjH\">https://t.co/yt9aNp5vjH</a></p>&mdash; G J Stokes (@GJStokes3) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GJStokes3/status/1422492971539202055?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">August 3, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></figure><p>Go and see what we see on Rachel's profile on <a href=\"https://foundation.app/@raecreate\">Foundation</a>. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-3.42.13-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"792\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-3.42.13-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-3.42.13-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-3.42.13-PM.png 1600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w2400/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-3.42.13-PM.png 2400w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><h3 id=\"mintface-sale-featurecryptoarte\">MintFace Sale Feature - CryptoArte</h3><p>Today's MintFace Sales feature is a forgotten collection that was first minted on the blockchain on the 4:04am 13th July 2018. Sebastián Brocher launched the first generative art project on Ethereum that day. 🤯 </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/unnamed-8.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"768\" height=\"432\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/unnamed-8.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/unnamed-8.png 768w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"><figcaption><a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/0xbace7e22f06554339911a03b8e0ae28203da9598/400\">Painting #400</a> was the first CryptoArte to be minted on the blockchain bought from Sebastian Broucher by <a href=\"https://opensea.io/Akwwong\">Akwwong</a>.</figcaption></figure><p>Painting #400 was the first to be minted. You could choose to mint any number you liked... and even today you can <a href=\"https://www.cryptoarte.io/gallery\">mint a digital artwork</a> straight from the <a href=\"https://www.cryptoarte.io/gallery\">original CryptoArte Gallery</a>. </p><p>There's even a spreadsheet because if you can pickup one of the 471 in the series that pre-date <a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/autoglyphs\">AutoGlyphs</a>, then you're the owner of digital art of historical note.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">🤝 Pre-AutoGlyph<br /><br />Painting #9867<br />by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/CryptoArte?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@CryptoArte</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/ayXvAUJ9H2\">https://t.co/ayXvAUJ9H2</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/sIF1GQk5Ki\">pic.twitter.com/sIF1GQk5Ki</a></p>&mdash; Silver Surfer (@7Surfer7Silver7) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/7Surfer7Silver7/status/1423126913015590913?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">August 5, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></figure><p>If you want to get 🧪molecular, there's a spreadsheet that correlates mint number to painting number. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/u/1/d/1QT_Rbn9jsuaVQ92uSRYZ0v7-ETJrnG7pu_NcfiLBLqs/htmlview#gid=0\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.24.19-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1556\" height=\"722\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.24.19-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.24.19-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.24.19-PM.png 1556w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></a><figcaption>Thank you to <a href=\"https://twitter.com/etheria_feed/status/1405558626463408129?s=20\">Etheria</a> for the spreadsheet</figcaption></figure><p>Early works are treasured by collectors of digital artwork. There are even statistics that track what work was released when. If you'd like to dig in more on the CryptoArte series, read \"<a href=\"https://medium.com/coinmonks/a-comprehensive-guide-to-cryptoarte-paintings-724783c87442\">A Comprehensive Guide To CryptoArte Paintings</a>.\" Be prepared to learn\n about prime numbers, hieroglyphic icons and golden miners. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.28.03-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"854\" height=\"504\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.28.03-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.28.03-PM.png 854w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>The artist is <a href=\"https://medium.com/@sebinatx\">Sebastián Brocher</a>, an Ethereum enthusiast and a technology entrepreneur with an artistic mind. When he was about 6 years of age, his Dad brought home a Commodore 128 computer and helped him code a program that played a J.S. Bach invention by following the instructions manual. </p><p>Ever since that day, Sebastián has always been fascinated by the intersection of computer science and art. Have a <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/episode/3Y0rYHIADWXfo9voI5ioKh?si=10137141df3342f3&amp;nd=1\">listen to an interview</a> he gave being interviewed by Adam McBride on 4th Aug 2021.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/0xbace7e22f06554339911a03b8e0ae28203da9598/9867\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/unnamed-9.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"768\" height=\"432\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/unnamed-9.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/unnamed-9.png 768w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></a><figcaption><a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/0xbace7e22f06554339911a03b8e0ae28203da9598/9867\">Painting #9867</a></figcaption></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.40.34-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1278\" height=\"1306\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.40.34-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.40.34-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.40.34-PM.png 1278w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"><figcaption>CryptoArte purchases by one collector on 5th Aug 2021</figcaption></figure><p>If you're into to vintage NFT, <a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/curiocardswrapper\">Curio Cards</a> is another series that holds fascination for me as they're the <a href=\"https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/standards/tokens/erc-721/\">first ERC-721 contract</a> on the blockchain. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.14.56-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1102\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.14.56-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.14.56-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.14.56-PM.png 1600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w2400/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.14.56-PM.png 2400w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Few have a visual aesthetic I can appreciate although CryptoArte gets close. The generative art has a hypnotising effect. </p><h3 id=\"mintface-artwork-featurebobbleheads\">MintFace Artwork Feature - Bobbleheads</h3><p><a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/0x495f947276749ce646f68ac8c248420045cb7b5e/20166578658462350495796695978459827162504313851036371438694107253028320968705\">One hundred Bobbleheads</a>. Wait... what's a Bobblehead? This single artwork was created by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ScottBatemanArt\">Scott Bateman</a>, and contains a montage of 100 Bobblehead paintings, rediscovered in his personal archive that goes back 15 years. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/E72tYqJWYAE2akB.jpeg\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"668\" height=\"945\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/E72tYqJWYAE2akB.jpeg 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/E72tYqJWYAE2akB.jpeg 668w\"></figure><p>The detail will be more visible on the signed A2 print that comes with the NFT.</p><p>Individually minted Bobbleheads invite you to walk in to their whimsical landscape of rainbow adorned homes and emotive vistas with a sprinking of optimism in each work.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.36.20-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"687\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.36.20-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.36.20-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.36.20-PM.png 1600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/2021/08/Screen-Shot-2021-08-05-at-4.36.20-PM.png 2376w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p></p><p><strong>Enjoying MintFace? Help keep it free by supporting the platform in one of two ways.</strong></p><p><strong>Art Collectors</strong> - you can become a member to receive a secret weekly MintFace  surfacing artwork that others have missed. No apes. No punks. Just quality art by quality artists.</p><p><strong>Artists</strong> - you can send any notes of appreciation to <em><strong>ryanj.eth</strong></em> in whatever form you feel reflects your art.</p><p>MintFace surfaces great artists and artworks so you don't have to. We also run the <a href=\"https://maven.com/cache/nft-digital-artist-economy\">Digital Artist Economy workshop</a> helping artists deserving of digital prominence create their first digital art through the <a href=\"https://maven.com/cache/nft-digital-artist-economy\">three week programme.</a> </p><p>Share it with an artist you'd like to see showing work next to you on an NFT marketplace.</p><p></p><p></p>"}